	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I'm not sure I understand the plugin system yet, does that mean the plugins have to be written in lua, can't do them in C?  Or is it like a DLL, where the language doesn't matter.</div>
<br />
<br />The plugin system is based off of XML with lua scripting only -- it is platform independent as it is processed directly by nesicide2, and not any outside libraries. Although it is scripted, it will have a lot of functionality and access to the actual UI and compiler. It's kinda hard to explain without you actually seeing it in action.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


